<i>noun</i>: 망령 [망ː녕], 노환 [노ː환], 노쇠 [노ː쇠/노ː쉐], 노망기 [노ː망끼], 노망 [노ː망] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>망령 [망ː녕]</dt><br>
<dd>senility</dd><br>
<dd>늙거나 정신이 흐려져서 말이나 행동이 정상적인 상태를 벗어남. 또는 그러한 말이나 행동.</dd><br>
<dd>Words or actions deviating from what is considered normal due to old age or a fuzzy mind, or such words or actions.</dd><br>
<dt>노환 [노ː환]</dt><br>
<dd>senility</dd><br>
<dd>(높임말로) 늙어서 몸이 약해지며 생기는 병.</dd><br>
<dd>(honorific) The weakening of the body as a result of old age.</dd><br>
<dt>노쇠 [노ː쇠/노ː쉐]</dt><br>
<dd>decrepitude; infirmity of old age; senility</dd><br>
<dd>늙어서 몸의 기운이 약함.</dd><br>
<dd>Being weak from aging.</dd><br>
<dt>노망기 [노ː망끼]</dt><br>
<dd>senility; second childhood</dd><br>
<dd>늙어서 정신이 흐려지고 말이나 행동이 정상을 벗어나는 낌새.</dd><br>
<dd>A hint of diminishing intelligence and saying or acting abnormally, due to aging.</dd><br>
<dt>노망 [노ː망]</dt><br>
<dd>dotage; senility</dd><br>
<dd>늙어서 정신이 흐려지고 말이나 행동이 정상이 아닌 상태.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which a person's mental acuity is weak and his/her words and behavior are abnormal as a result of old age.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>